{"id":1725641,"retrievedAt":"2026-07-04T12:27:36.517Z","response":{"adult":false,"backdrop_path":"/hFX7aU68N45z2y0ZfX3ioiXQAG7.jpg","belongs_to_collection":null,"budget":0,"genres":[{"id":99,"name":"Documentary"}],"homepage":"https://www.soshimalaya.org/en/","id":1725641,"imdb_id":"tt43643774","origin_country":["ES"],"original_language":"es","original_title":"La Voz de Iñaki","overview":"This 2008 documentary traces the journey of mountaineer Iñaki Ochoa de Olza Seguin. Rather than recounting his death, the film focuses on his life, drawing on a wide range of archival materials: recordings of lectures made by his father, photos sent by friends, period footage, and 8mm home movies. Iñaki’s voice—culled from these materials—challenges our complacency and speaks of his connection to Navarre, his family, and the mountains. Through this relationship with the mountains, the film explores joy, pain, the contrast between a life lived intensely and a conventional, comfortable existence, as well as happiness and death. This tribute film premiered at the Baluarte Auditorium in Pamplona in 2008, during the ceremony awarding medals for sporting merit to Iñaki himself and to everyone who had taken part in his rescue.","popularity":0,"poster_path":"/ypO3ol2Z66jX5c0MCfydNHfYKPo.jpg","production_companies":[{"id":64908,"logo_path":"/2riyOGEtRH6tTegkAsdAqp3lI0p.png","name":"Arena Comunicación Audiovisual","origin_country":"ES"}],"production_countries":[{"iso_3166_1":"ES","name":"Spain"}],"release_date":"2008-01-01","revenue":0,"runtime":32,"softcore":false,"spoken_languages":[{"english_name":"Spanish","iso_639_1":"es","name":"Español"}],"status":"Released","tagline":"","title":"Iñaki's Voice","video":false,"vote_average":10,"vote_count":1,"alternative_titles":{"titles":[]},"credits":{"cast":[{"adult":false,"gender":2,"id":1119638,"known_for_department":"Acting","name":"Iñaki Ochoa de Olza","original_name":"Iñaki Ochoa de Olza","popularity":0.0946,"profile_path":"/4AqbZRsRpIfVLc1UVtyn